-- Spanish Prosecutor Calls for Probe of Savings Banks, Europa Says
-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 2012-05-20T10:40:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-20/spanish-prosecutor-calls-for-probe-of-savings-banks-europa-says.html
Spain ’s state prosecutor, Eduardo
Torres-Dulce, has called for an investigation into the
management of the nation’s savings banks,  Europa Press  reported,
citing an interview.  Torres-Dulce ordered the anti-corruption prosecutor,
Antonio Salinas, to investigate “penal responsibility that may
derive from the management of the savings banks,” the Madrid-
based news service reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas in Madrid at 
 erossthomas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  